      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You're right to feel the weight of this, but the idea that you're taking up space is a cruel lie that ignores how your presence fills the gaps in other people's lives. If you truly vanished tomorrow, the city wouldn't just remain unchanged; it would lose a unique piece of its collective story that no one else can replace. The only way to truly stop feeling like a ghost is to keep showing up, even when it hurts, because your existence is the only thing that makes this moment real for everyone else.",
